BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:k113rMmvgVfCwKD-72dZS
SUMMARY:Washington Ensemble Theater Playwright Showcase
DTSTAMP:20260322T034727Z
DTSTART:20260321T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:WETWorks \\nA Playwright-in-Residence program \\nConceived and 
	Curated by Nelle Tankus and Anamaria Guerzon \\nIn Partnership with Hugo H
	ouse \\nFALL 2025- SPRING 2026 | Hugo House \\n  \\nWETWorks is our brand 
	new Playwright-in-Residence program\\\, in partnership with Hugo House. Ov
	er the next year\\\, WET will collaborate with three playwrights for a thr
	ee-month paid residency each. They will be provided space to write and a c
	reative team\\\, culminating in a final presentation at Hugo House at the 
	end of their tenure. WETWorks provides the tangible resources\\\, communit
	y connections\\\, and creative space needed for Seattle playwrights. With 
	this program we hope to answer a call for Seattle based playwriting opport
	unity\\\, as well as echo the Pacific Northwest lens and experience back t
	o ourselves. \\n \\nPlaywright for March 20th play: Isabelle Bushue \\nPla
	y Name: Extraordinary Outstanding Luck \\nSynopsis: A Chinese adoptee come
	s to terms with her childhood and explores how to live without knowing her
	 origins. \\nBuy tickets here! \\n \\nEvent Schedule: \\nDoors Open: 6:00 
	PM \\nEvent Start: 7:00 PM \\nEvent End: 9:00 PM\n\nhttps://hugohouse.org/
	event/washington-ensemble-theater-playwright-showcase_2026-03-21/\n\nFrom 
	Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/washington-ensemble-theater-playwright-show
	case_2026-03-21/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
